main event: An observer reported seeing a very large unidentified object with many bright lights in Sebeka, Minnesota on March 15, 1967.
interesting points: The object was described as having lights of many colors and very bright lights on the top., The observer stated that the object had very slight motion before disappearing in a bright light., The estimated speed of the object was around 35 m.p.h., The observer was a 47-year-old female farmer who first thought it might be a helicopter but noticed it had no rotor blades., The sighting was reported to authorities on March 16, 1967, and was classified as a possible aircraft.
sighted object: a large unidentified flying object with many bright lights
